channel.title: Hacking RS2
channel.description:
Hello. I am one of those guys who tries hard in rs2 and doesnt make any money. I have seen the program Cheat Engine 5.3 used to dupe money, but you can't trade with it. i was wondering if there was a program that dupes money and works. i was also wondering if anyone knew any bots to help in mining, smithing, woodcutting, and / or fishing.
Thanks, :confused: Burns :confused:

item.title: Hacking RS2
item.dc:creator: @exe626 exe626
item.description:
@exe626 wrote:

On a forum that has nothing to do with Jagex or Runescape, a guy posted his ideas on editing packets to give different items when you perform certain task(quest, skills). He was working on changing what farming gives you when you do it, but he could never figure it out.

“i found all of the proper cases, found all the proper id’s. i just cant seem to trick the server into giving me what i want”

So. If you trick the server, make it think you’re getting 1 thing, while receiving another, you could dupe. But this is only theoretical.

Read full topic

You can bug dupe, but it requires many experimental things. You have to do it at the time the server will only save if you logout, and not save (in case of death), when you’re forced to logout.

yup ill actully done that before it was really cool .

i did it with my friend and to bad i was only around lvl 45 when it happend. so the items were steel long and some type of bronze i cant remember.

How it happened was. i logged on then went to the bank there was like 30+ people there (varrock east bank on F2P) so i got the stuff out ment up with my friend right outside the bank traded him and i dont remember why but right when i traded him i logged off fast. then got back on as normal and weridly noticed that my items were back. and so i gave him the new dup. items so he had 2 of each… to bad it only happened once =(

item.title: Hacking RS2
item.dc:creator: @Hyjall Hyjall
item.description:
@Hyjall wrote:

[quote=“Swordskid61, post:10, topic:163801”][quote author=bburns link=topic=222514.msg1923273#msg1923273 date=1197261755]
I have seen the program Cheat Engine 5.3 used to dupe money, but you can’t trade with it.
[/quote]
make someone sell to shop and you buy it?[/quote]

…

Let’s get this clear, the client provides you with only a visual representation of the item you have, there is no important character info stored on your local computer. How would duplicating the visual representation of the item have any effect on the server whatsoever. Seriously, Cheat Engine is one of the most wide known cheats out there, did you really think no one in the million player base of runescape would abused it by duping thousands of rare items by now?
